text: The William F. and Julia Crome House is a historic house located at 305 South Second Street in Clinton, Henry County, Missouri. == Description and history == It was built in 1904, and is two-story, American Foursquare style brick dwelling with Colonial Revival style design elements. It has an intersecting hip roof with five dormers and a full-width front porch. Also on the property is a contributing brick garage. (includes 8 photographs from 1996) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places on March 25, 1999. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Colonial Revival architecture in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1904 Category:Buildings and structures in Henry County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Henry County, Missouri Category:American Foursquare architecture
